29#define GEN8_LR_CONTEXT_ALIGN 4096
30#define GEN8_CSB_ENTRIES 6
31#define GEN8_CSB_PTR_MASK 0x07

33/* Execlists regs */
34#define RING_ELSP(ring) ((ring)->mmio_base+0x230)
35#define RING_EXECLIST_STATUS_LO(ring) ((ring)->mmio_base+0x234)
36#define RING_EXECLIST_STATUS_HI(ring) ((ring)->mmio_base+0x234 + 4)
37#define RING_CONTEXT_CONTROL(ring) ((ring)->mmio_base+0x244)
38#define CTX_CTRL_INHIBIT_SYN_CTX_SWITCH (1 << 3)
39#define CTX_CTRL_ENGINE_CTX_RESTORE_INHIBIT (1 << 0)
40#define CTX_CTRL_RS_CTX_ENABLE (1 << 1)
41#define RING_CONTEXT_STATUS_BUF_LO(ring, i) ((ring)->mmio_base+0x370 + (i) * 8)
42#define RING_CONTEXT_STATUS_BUF_HI(ring, i) ((ring)->mmio_base+0x370 + (i) * 8 + 4)
43#define RING_CONTEXT_STATUS_PTR(ring) ((ring)->mmio_base+0x3a0)

45/* Logical Rings */
46int intel_logical_ring_alloc_request_extras(struct drm_i915_gem_request *request);
47int intel_logical_ring_reserve_space(struct drm_i915_gem_request *request);
48void intel_logical_ring_stop(struct intel_engine_cs *ring);
49void intel_logical_ring_cleanup(struct intel_engine_cs *ring);
50int intel_logical_rings_init(struct drm_device *dev);
51int intel_logical_ring_begin(struct drm_i915_gem_request *req, int num_dwords);
52
53int logical_ring_flush_all_caches(struct drm_i915_gem_request *req);
54/**
55 * intel_logical_ring_advance() - advance the ringbuffer tail
56 * @ringbuf: Ringbuffer to advance.
57 *
58 * The tail is only updated in our logical ringbuffer struct.
59 */
60static inline void intel_logical_ring_advance(struct intel_ringbuffer *ringbuf)
61{
62 ringbuf->tail &= ringbuf->size - 1;
63}
64/**
65 * intel_logical_ring_emit() - write a DWORD to the ringbuffer.
66 * @ringbuf: Ringbuffer to write to.
67 * @data: DWORD to write.
68 */
69static inline void intel_logical_ring_emit(struct intel_ringbuffer *ringbuf,
70 u32 data)
71{
72#ifdef __NetBSD__
73 bus_space_write_4(ringbuf->bst, ringbuf->bsh, ringbuf->tail, data);
74#else
75 iowrite32(data, ringbuf->virtual_start + ringbuf->tail);
76#endif
77 ringbuf->tail += 4;
78}
